<h2>What Is the Answer Economy?</h2>
<p>The answer economy is a market where AI systems generate direct answers to user questions instead of directing users to websites. The user gets what they need without clicking a link. The AI cites sources inline, but most users never visit those sources.</p>
<p>This is a structural change, not a trend. For 25 years, the internet ran on the <strong>link economy</strong>. Create content, earn links, rank in search results, get clicks. Every business model from media to ecommerce depended on that flow.</p>
<p>The answer economy replaces that flow. Now AI engines read your content, extract the answer, and deliver it to the user. The user gets value. You get a citation. Maybe.</p>
