<h2>How the Answer Economy Changes Content Strategy</h2>
<p>Most content strategies optimize for clicks. Write a blog post, rank it, drive traffic, convert visitors. That playbook still works for some queries. But for the 65% that end without a click, you need a different approach.</p>
<h3>From Traffic to Trust</h3>
<p>The old metric was "how much traffic does this page drive?" The new metric is "does AI cite this page when someone asks a question?"</p>
<p>Traffic-focused content prioritizes keyword volume, word count, and click-bait titles. Answer-economy content prioritizes fact density, structure, and brand authority.</p>
<p>Here is the practical difference:</p>
